<Challenge Title="Challenge Area of a Circle">
    <Text>
        In this challenge, you will write a program to calculate the area of a circle.
    </Text>
    <TaskList Name="Area of a Circle">
        <TaskItem Name="Create a New Project">Create a new project called "Circle Analyzer"</TaskItem>
        <Text>Your program should: </Text>
        <TaskItem Name="Display">Displays a welcome message.</TaskItem>
        <TaskItem Name="Prompt">Prompts the user to enter the <b>diameter</b> of a circle</TaskItem>
        <TaskItem Name="Float diameter">Creates a variable to store the user's input</TaskItem>
        <TaskItem Name="Float Radius">Create and initialize a variable to store the radius of the circle (<Code>diameter / 2</Code>)</TaskItem>
        <TaskItem Name="Float Pi">Using the <Code>Math</Code>, calculate the area of the circle.</TaskItem>
        <TaskItem Name="Store Pi">Store the result in a variable.</TaskItem>
        <TaskItem Name="Display Radius">Display a message informing the user the radius of the circle.</TaskItem>
        <TaskItem Name="Display Area">Finally, display a message informing the user the area of the circle.</TaskItem>
    </TaskList>
</Challenge>